script = ExtResource("1_1gwqn")
questions_data = "#1
How data is represented in raster images?
<y> by storing color data in every pixel
<n> by drawing shapes and filling them later
<n> by assigning each pixel with a unique color a number
<y> most commonly each pixel has three channels: red, green, blue
<e>

#2
What is color depth?
<n> how many pixels there are in the image.
<y> how many bits each pixel takes
<y> how many possible colors the image can represent 
<n> how many color channels the image has
<e>

#3
What is image resolution?
<y> total number of pixels in the image
<y> pixels along width and height of the image
<y> how many color channels the image has
<n> how many bits each pixel takes
<e>

#4
Which of the following are text encodings?
<y> ASCII
<y> Unicode
<n> SSH
<n> CMYK
<e>

#5
On which text encoding there are more possible characters?
<n> ASCII
<y> Unicode
<n> SSH
<n> CMYK
<e>

#6
Which encoding takes only 1 byte for each character?
<y> ASCII
<n> Unicode
<n> SSH
<n> CMYK
<e>

#7
Which encoding may take up to 4 bytes for each character?
<n> ASCII
<y> Unicode
<n> SSH
<n> CMYK
<e>

#8 
How sound is represented?
<y> by taking snapshots of sound wave
<y> as a sequence of samples on some frequency
<n> the same as video, moving images
<n> as a perfect copy of sound wave
<e>

#9 
What is sample rate?
<y> How often samples are taken
<y> The quality of the sound
<n> How many bits are needed for each sample
<n> The frequency of the sound wave
<e>

#10
What is sample resolution?
<n> How often samples are taken
<y> The quality of the sound
<y> How many bits are needed for each sample
<n> The frequency of the sound wave
<e>
